2014-10~12
http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/general/807156/china-expels-french-journalist

Bangkok Post
In an image taken from China Central Television, Uighurs deported from Thailand in July this year are shown being removed from a China Southern Airlines plane at an unidentified location in China. Beijing alleged that some of the Uighurs who had entered Thailand illegally intended to travel to Turkey and then go to join jihadist fighters in Syria and Iraq. (Reuters Photo)

Expecting the move, Ursula Gauthier, a long-time journalist for the French news magazine L'Obs, said late Friday night that she was prepared to leave China.

